file: prompts/README.md
behavior: Documents the plain-markdown agent prompts directory (leaf summarizer, rollup summarizer, auditor) and the contract that separates prompt content from runner code.
edit_notes:
  - Prompts are loaded verbatim at runtime as the system prompt; runners must not embed or append instructions to prompt content — dynamic data belongs only in the user message.
  - When a prompt file changes meaningfully, the existing summary tree must be re-run through the summarizer to match the new standard; no in-file version numbers, git history is the log.
functions:
invariants:
  - Runner code must not contain parsing, validation, or retry logic that belongs in these prompt files, nor task-specific dynamic data (file paths, diffs).
  - Prompt files must remain portable across model upgrades (no model-specific instructions).
external_deps: